After playing it for 4 hours, here are my thoughts:
- there are few material combinations: some raw materials can be combined to only one or two new items;
- the only challenge I had while playing was at night. Fighting against hordes of enemies isn't bad but if that is all, the game gets boring. A cave full of traps, tougher critters with new attack patterns or a new method of exploration would give some flavor to it;
- there are also few enemy types; some enemies could shoot charged wall-penetrating bullets or cause status debuffs instead just having more HP / cause more damage / shoot more bullets;
- it needs more weapons/ways to defend yourself; close ranged weapon, hidden abilities, trap turrets, force fields are some examples that would be very nice to add. I know you could just place a lot of turrets around you, but it does become dull.

It need some improvements, but there is a lot of potential for this game.
